docs.snippet: Your daily look at late-breaking news, upcoming events and the stories that will be talked about today:

North Korea has agreed to hold high-level talks with South Korea on March 29 at the border truce village of Panmunjom to prepare for a summit of their leaders planned for April, the South said on Saturday.

headline.print_headline: South Korea Says North Agrees to Hold Summit Preparation Talks on March 29
headline.main: South Korea Says North Agrees to Hold Summit Preparation Talks on March 29

docs.snippet: The Justice Department's internal watchdog said Wednesday it will examine Republican complaints of FBI misconduct in the early stages of the Russia investigation.

headline.print_headline: Justice Watchdog Probes Charges of FBI Abuse in Russia Case
headline.main: Justice Watchdog Probes Charges of FBI Abuse in Russia Case

docs.snippet: To Wall Street money managers who make bets for a living, U.S. President Donald Trump's aggressive stance against China on trade looks like a high-stakes poker hand - but they believe  they can play it for all it's worth.

headline.print_headline: On China Trade Clash, Wall Street Embraces Trump's Poker Face
headline.main: On China Trade Clash, Wall Street Embraces Trump's Poker Face

docs.snippet: The Singapore-based chip maker had sought to complete the biggest technology deal in history, but the White House blocked it, citing threats to U.S. national security.

headline.main: Broadcom Drops Bid for Qualcomm After Trump’s Intervention

docs.snippet: Anyone looking for a pattern should focus squarely on the man behind the desk in the Oval Office. “I like conflict,” President Trump said.

headline.print_headline: As White House’s Revolving Door Whirls, Chaos Is the Only Constant
headline.main: As White House’s Revolving Door Whirls, Chaos Is the Only Constant

docs.snippet: All 435 House seats are up for grabs, but only about 48 seats are considered competitive.

headline.main: To Reclaim the House, Democrats Need to Flip 24 G.O.P. Seats. 25 Are in Clinton Territory.

docs.snippet: Anticipating an unpredictable president's next moves, U.S. officials have started actively planning for the likelihood that Donald Trump will announce next month that the U.S. is withdrawing from the Iran nuclear deal.

headline.print_headline: Anticipating Trump's Next Move, Aides Prep Iran Deal Pullout
headline.main: Anticipating Trump's Next Move, Aides Prep Iran Deal Pullout

docs.snippet: Angela Merkel was right when she said, “We Europeans must really take our destiny into our own hands.”

headline.print_headline: Why Europe’s Giving Up on Trump’s America
headline.main: Why Europe Is Giving Up on Trump’s America
